f, g:\Bbb R \to \Bbb R
x, y\in \Bbb R
 |f(x+y)-f(x)g(y)|\le \frac 1 4 
x, y\in \Bbb R
 |f(x)||1-g(y)|\le \frac 1 4 
f(x)=\frac{\sin x}4
g(x)=\cos x
x=\frac{\pi}2
y=\pi
\left|f(x+y)-f(x)g(y)\right|=\frac14\left|\sin(x+y)-\sin x\cos y\right|= \frac14\left|\sin y\cos x\right|\le \frac14
\left|f(\frac{\pi}2)\right|\left|1-g(\pi)\right|=\left|\frac{1}4\right|\left|2\right|=\frac12> \frac14
